Visualizing Cities by Roads¶

It's interesting how every city has it's own unique pattern of roads. Each network forms a distinct skelatal framework which supports the living organism that is a bustling city.

G = ox.graph_from_point([32.755263, -117.134800], distance=15000, network_type='drive') #San Diego
fig, ax = ox.plot_graph(G,edge_alpha=1, node_alpha=0,fig_height=15, dpi=300);
fig.tight_layout()
